<%- include('partials/header') %>

<h1>About <%= APP.NAME %></h1>

<!-- Tagline -->
<div class="container">
  <h2>Capture now. Sync later.</h2>
  <p>
    Inboxios is an
    <strong> open-source, offline-first task manager</strong> designed to make
    task capture fast, reliable, and distraction-free. It integrates with Notion
    while ensuring that creating a task never depends on having a perfect
    internet connection.
  </p>
  <div class="quote">
    <h3 class="quote-title">The philosophy is simple:</h3>
    <p class="quote-body">
      Your productivity shouldn't stop because your connection does.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Problem -->
<div class="container">
  <h2>The Problem</h2>
  <p>
    Most productivity applications rely on a constant internet connection. Even
    a brief network interruption can slow down or completely interrupt your
    workflow.
  </p>
  <p>
    When your goal is simply to capture an idea before you forget it, waiting
    for an API request is unnecessary friction.
  </p>
  <p class="highlight">Inboxios aims to eliminate that friction.</p>
</div>

<!-- Solution -->
<div class="container">
  <h2>The Solution</h2>
  <p>Inboxios follows an <strong>offline-first</strong> approach.</p>
  <p>
    Every task is designed to be captured instantly and stored locally first.
    Synchronization with Notion happens separately, allowing you to continue
    working without interruption.
  </p>
  <p>This means you can:</p>
  <ul class="simple-list">
    <li>Capture tasks instantly</li>
    <li>Continue working offline</li>
    <li>Synchronize changes when a connection becomes available</li>
    <li>Keep your workflow uninterrupted</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The application treats synchronization as a background process rather than
    something that blocks the user.
  </p>
</div>

<!-- Working -->
<div class="container">
  <h2>How <%= APP.NAME %> Works</h2>
  <div class="flowchart">
    <div class="step">Create Task</div>
    <div class="step">Inboxios</div>
    <div class="step">Local Storage</div>
    <div class="step">Synchronization Queue</div>
    <div class="step">Notion API</div>
    <div class="step">Your Notion Workspace</div>
  </div>
  <p>
    The long-term goal is to make synchronization automatic and resilient,
    ensuring that your local data and Notion remain in sync with minimal user
    interaction.
  </p>
</div>

<!-- Tech Stack -->
<div class="container">
  <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
  <p>
    Inboxios is built with a modern JavaScript stack focused on simplicity and
    maintainability.
  </p>
  <dl class="tech-dl">
    <dt>Node.js</dt>
    <dd>JavaScript runtime</dd>
    <dt>Express</dt>
    <dd>Web framework</dd>
    <dt>EJS</dt>
    <dd>Server-side rendering</dd>
    <dt>Axios</dt>
    <dd>Communication with the Notion API</dd>
    <dt>Notion API</dt>
    <dd>Task storage and synchronization</dd>
    <dt>CSS</dt>
    <dd>Responsive user interface</dd>
  </dl>
  <p>
    The project intentionally avoids unnecessary complexity while maintaining a
    modular architecture.
  </p>
</div>

<!-- Reason for Building -->
<div class="container">
  <h2>Why I Built <%= APP.NAME %></h2>
  <p>
    Inboxios began as a way to explore REST APIs and backend development with
    Express.
  </p>

  <p>
    As the project grew, it became an opportunity to experiment with software
    architecture, server-side rendering, synchronization strategies, and
    building production-style web applications.
  </p>

  <p>
    Rather than simply connecting a frontend to an API, the goal is to
    understand how real-world applications are designed, structured, and
    maintained.
  </p>
</div>

<!-- Open Source -->
<div class="container">
  <h2>Open Source</h2>
  <p>Inboxios is an open-source project.</p>

  <p>
    Whether you're looking to learn Express, explore the Notion API, or
    contribute ideas, you're welcome to explore the project.
  </p>
  <h3>Resources</h3>
  <ul class="btn-group">
    <li class="icon-text">
      <a
        href="<%= APP.LINKS.DOCS %>"
        class="btn"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >Documentation</a
      >
    </li>
    <li class="icon-text">
      <a
        href="<%= APP.LINKS.GITHUB %>"
        class="btn"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >GitHub Repository</a
      >
    </li>
    <li class="icon-text">
      <a
        href="<%= APP.LINKS.ISSUES %>"
        class="btn"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >Report an Issue</a
      >
    </li>
    <li class="icon-text">
      <a
        href="<%= APP.LINKS.TEMPLATE %>"
        class="btn"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >Notion Template</a
      >
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
